        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on JM’s review of <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi>, vol. 2 [<hi rend="italic">Pall Mall Gaz.</hi> 13 (1871): 1358–9].</p> 
            <p>Mistake CD made "in speaking of greatest happiness as the foundation of morals" is unintelligible to CD. Discusses J. S. Mill’s view of moral feelings as natural. Discusses basis of conscience.</p>
            <p>Glad to read remarks on hive-bees.</p>
        </abstract>
